We recommended that the procuring entity and the BAC strictly adhere to all provisions of law, rules and regulations pertaining to procurement since the interest of the city government, being a political subdivision of the government, at all times be protected. For the inconsistencies noted, the city government should be guided by the following:

A comprehensive Annual Procurement Plan be prepared consistent with the annual Budget and once the APP is final and approved, it shall be submitted to the GPPB on or before the end of January of the budget year and it shall also be posted in the GPPB website. In this way, transparency as a governing principle in public procurement and compliance to the rule of law are recognized and adopted; 

The procuring entity should prepare the technical specifications involved in the construction of infrastructure projects to suit the works at hand; 

Management should refrain from indicating the brand names of goods to be procured to ensure a more competitive bidding and that prices and quality of items availed of are the most advantageous to the government; 

Notices of Award must be posted within the required time frame; and 

For Small Value Procurements with ABC above P 50,000.00, the BAC Secretariat should post, for information purposes, the invitation or request for submission of price quotations/ proposals and Notice of Award in the agency website and at any conspicuous place reserved for the purpose in the premises of the procuring entity.

